Police In Mombasa Have Gunned Down Two Suspected Robbers Near Shimo La Tewa Maximum Prison This Evening. Kisauni OCPD, Julius Kiragu Confirmed The Incident Saying There Was An Exchange Of Fire Between The Officers And The Suspects. The OCPD Says He Believed The Gang Is Responsible For Robberies At Mpsea Shops In The Area As Well As The Murder To Mpesa Operators Who Were Killed Last Week. A Pistol Was Recovered From The Slain Suspects.